6,4,3,1]\nOutput: 0\nExplanation: In this case, no transactions are done and the max profit = 0.\n\n \nConstraints:\n\n1 <= prices.length <= 105\n0 <= prices[i] <= 104\n\n\n\n### Format: You will use the following starter code to write the solution to the problem and enclose your code within delimiters.\n```python\nclass Solution:\n    def maxProfit(self, prices: List[int]) -> int:\n        \n```\n\n### Answer: (use the provided format with backticks)\n", "response": "```python\nfrom typing import List\n\nclass Solution:\n    def maxProfit(self, prices: List[int]) -> int:\n        if not prices:\n            return 0\n        \n        min_price = prices[0]\n        max_profit = 0\n        \n        for price in prices:\n            if price < min_price:\n                min_price = price\n            elif price - min_price > max_profit:\n                max_profit = price - min_price\n        \n        return max_profit\n```\n\nThis solution iterates through the list of prices, keeping track of the minimum price encountered so far and the maximum profit that can be achieved by selling at the current price after buying at the minimum price seen so far. The time complexity is O(n), where n is the length of the prices list, and the space complexity is O(1).", "estimated_date": 1438905600000}